<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[794,1418,1274,1555]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Although most species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik" authorityYear="2005" box="[1266,1354,1274,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1266,1354,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Alterosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have fairly restricted distributions in pristine Atlantic Forest streams, 
<taxonomicName authority="Blahnik (2005)" authorityName="Blahnik" authorityYear="2005" box="[892,1158,1338,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis box="[892,992,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. falcata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blahnik, R. J." box="[999,1158,1338,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref3747" refString="Blahnik, R. J. 2005. Alterosa, a new caddisfly genus from Brazil (Trichoptera: Philopotamidae). Zootaxa, 991: 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="2005">Blahnik (2005)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
can be considered one of the few exceptions. Originally described from several locations in 
<collectingRegion box="[931,1078,1402,1427]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1088,1248,1402,1427]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1307,1417,1402,1427]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
states (
<bibRefCitation author="Blahnik, R. J." box="[874,1032,1434,1459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref3747" refString="Blahnik, R. J. 2005. Alterosa, a new caddisfly genus from Brazil (Trichoptera: Philopotamidae). Zootaxa, 991: 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="2005">Blahnik, 2005</bibRefCitation>
), its distribution was extended to other areas of these states (
<bibRefCitation author="Dumas, L. L. &amp; Jardim, G. A. &amp; Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." box="[1099,1306,1466,1491]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="355 - 376" refId="ref3985" refString="Dumas, L. L.; Jardim, G. A.; Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. 2009. Tricopteros (Insecta: Trichoptera) do Estado do Rio de Janeiro: Lista de especies e novos registros. Arquivos do Museu Nacional, 67 (3 - 4): 355 - 376." type="journal article" year="2009">
Dumas 
<emphasis box="[1186,1243,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al.,</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dumas, L. L. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref3828" refString="Dumas, L. L. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. 2012. Faunistic catalog of the caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) of Parque Nacional do Itatiaia and its surroundings in southeastern Brazil. Journal of Insect Science, 12 (25): 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2012">Dumas &amp; Nessimian, 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Herein, we record this species for the first time from 
<collectingRegion box="[957,1171,1530,1555]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Espírito Santo state</collectingRegion>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1332,1394,1530,1555]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
